# QML Standards

## Style
- Qt Quick Controls 2, `Material.Dark` theme, `Material.accent: Material.Teal`
- `camelCase` for all `id:` values
- Components in separate files under `src/ui/components/`
- No business logic in QML — call `Q_INVOKABLE` C++ methods; only bindings and visual state in QML

## Layout
- Use `ColumnLayout`, `RowLayout`, `GridLayout` for responsive layouts
- `anchors.fill: parent` for root items in a page/tab
- `spacing: 12` as default; `topPadding/bottomPadding: 16` for content areas

## Data Binding
- Bind directly to `controller.*` context property: `text: controller.deviceModel`
- Update via `onEditingFinished` or `onActivated`, not `onTextChanged` (avoid feedback loops)
- Use `Connections { target: controller }` for signals from C++

## Example: editable ComboBox+TextField combo
```qml
RowLayout {
    ComboBox {
        id: driverCombo
        model: controller.driverPresets()
        onActivated: controller.setCurrentSubsystemDriver(currentText)
    }
    TextField {
        placeholderText: "или введите вручную"
        onEditingFinished: controller.setCurrentSubsystemDriver(text)
    }
}
```

## File Operations (FileDialog)
```qml
FileDialog {
    id: openDialog
    title: "Открыть отчёт"
    nameFilters: ["Отчёт (*.txt)", "Все файлы (*)"]
    onAccepted: controller.openFile(selectedFile)
}
```
